d 'XTCSPQARDL': module to perform Cross-Sectionally Augmented Panel Quantile ARDL, Quantile CCE Mean Group, and Quantile CCE Pooled Mean Group Estimation
d
d	 xtcspqardl implements two estimators for dynamic
d heterogeneous panel data models with	  cross-sectional
d dependence at the quantile level: CS-PQARDL (Cross-Sectionally
d Augmented Panel Quantile ARDL):  Extends the panel quantile ARDL 
d	framework by augmenting unit-specific regressions with
d cross-sectional averages (CSA) of the        dependent and
d independent variables, following Pesaran (2006) and Chudik and
d Pesaran (2015).	 This absorbs unobserved common factors
d that induce cross-sectional dependence, producing	  
d consistent estimates under factor structures. CSA enter the
d long-run equation (or ECT in ECM	  form), but are excluded
d from short-run dynamics. QCCEMG (Quantile CCE Mean Group): 
d Implements the Quantile Common Correlated Effects Mean Group	   
d   estimator of Harding, Lamarche, and Pesaran (2018). This is a
d dynamic panel quantile regression	   model where unobserved
d common factors are proxied by CSA and their lags. Unit-specific
d quantile	  regressions are averaged using the Mean Group
d approach, with inference based on the        nonparametric
d between-group variance (Theorem 4 of HLP 2018). Both estimators
d handle heterogeneous slope coefficients across panels, permit
d quantile-varying    parameters, and are robust to cross-sectional
d dependence generated by unobserved common factors. QCCEPMG
d (Quantile CCE Pooled Mean Group):  Implements the pooled version
d of the QCCEMG estimator,	  following Pesaran (2006) CCEP
d methodology adapted to the quantile setting. Individual quantile 
d	regressions are estimated identically to QCCEMG, but the
d Mean Group averaging and inference	    follow the Pooled Mean
d Group approach. Under slope homogeneity, the QCCEPMG estimator
d achieves	  √(NT) convergence compared to √N for QCCEMG.
d All three estimators handle heterogeneous slope coefficients
d across panels, permit quantile-varying    parameters, and are
d robust to cross-sectional dependence generated by unobserved
d common factors. 
d
d KW: ARDL
d KW: autoregressive
d KW: panel data
d KW: quantile regression
d KW: mean group
d KW: pooled mean group
d
d Requires: Stata version 15.1
d
d Distribution-Date: 20260225
d
d Author:   Merwan Roudane, NA
d Support: email  merwanroudane920@@gmail.com
d
